eriment of Hershey and Chase -\n(a) Centrifugation, blending, infection\n(b) Infection, blending, centrifugation\n(c) Blending, infection, centrifugation\n(d) Infection, centrifugation and blending\n\n183. Radioisotope incorporated in protein during blending experiment is -\n(a) SО“ГҮГҰ35\n(b) PО“ГҮГҰ32\n(c) IО“ГҮГҰ32\n(d) None\n\n184. In Hershey and Chase experiment Bacteriophage with radiolabeled protein, after\ncentrifugation radioactivity appears in -\n(a) Radioactive sulphur in pellet\n(b) Radioactive phosphorus in supernatant\n(c) Radioactive sulphur in supernatant\n(d) Radioactive phosphorus in pellet\n\n185. If radioactivity of phosphorus is observed in supernatant in Hershey and Chase\nexperiment then inference is -\n(a) DNA is genetic material\n(b) RNA is genetic material\n(c) Protein is genetic material\n(d) All\n\n186. RNA is genetic material in -\n(a) QB bacteriophage\n(b) TMV\n(c) HIV\n(d) All\n\n187. Which feature of genetic material is useful for evolution -\n(a) Slow change\n(b) Express itself\n(c) Chemically stable\n(d) Generate its replica\n\n188. Biomacromolecule/s which have ability to make its copies -\n(a) DNA\n(b) RNA\n(c) Proteins\n(d) Both (a) and (b)\n\n189. 2'-OH group in RNA has effect -\n(a) Make it labile\n(b) Prone to degradation\n(c) Make it reactive\n(d) All\n\n190. Mark the incorrect statement -\n(a) DNA is chemically less reactive than RNA\n(b) DNA is structurally more stable than RNA\n(c) DNA is not catalytically active\n(d) RNA is catalytically inactive\n\n191. Which of the following is least thermostable -\n(a) DNA\n(b) RNA\n(c) Protein\n(d) All\n\n192. DNA evolved from RNA by -\n(a) Chemical modification\n(b) Structural change\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) None\n\n193. For transmission of character which is better -\n(a) DNA\n(b) RNA\n(c) Protein\n(d) All\n\n194. Which of the following process evolved around RNA -\n(a) Splicing\n(b) Translation\n(c) Initial metabolism\n(d) All\n\n195. DNA resist change by evolving -\n(a) Double strand\n(b) Repair\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) None\n\n196. Which is catalytically active -\n(a) DNA\n(b) RNA\n(c) Protein\n(d) Both (b) and (c)\n\n197. In Hershey and Chase experiment if blending is not done -\n(a) Supernatant show radioactivity of sulphur\n(b) Supernatant show radioactivity of phosphorus\n(c) Pellet show radioactivity from both sulphur and phosphorus\n(d) All are correct\n\n198. Which of the following is transcriptionally inactive -\n(a) Heterochromatin\n(b) Euchromatin\n(c) Chromosome\n(d) Both (a) and (c)\n\n199. According to Griffith transforming principle is -\n(a) DNA\n(b) RNA\n(c) Protein\n(d) Unknown\n\n200. If heat killed R-strain of Streptococcus along with live R-strain injected in mice then\nwhich is true -\n(a) Mice die due to pneumoniae and transformation occur\n(b) Mice alive and transformation occur\n(c) Mice die due to pneumoniae and no transformation occur\n(d) Mice die due to pneumoniae and from dead mice live R-strain obtained\n\n201. Smooth strain of Streptococcus (S-strain) is due to -\n(a) Protein\n(b) Mucopolysaccharide\n(c) Lipid\n(d) Nucleic acid\n\n202. DNA as transforming principle is proved by -\n(a) Avery, McCarty, Macleod\n(b) Griffith\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) Hershey and Chase\n\n203. In linear DNA of 200 base pair the number of phosphodiester bond is -\n(a) 198\n(b) 201\n(c) 199\n(d) 398\n\n204. Number of nucleotides in DNA is equal to -\n(a) Phosphodiester linkage\n(b) Covalent bonds\n(c) Nitrogenous bases\n(d) Hydrogen bond\n\n205. Which of the following is Circular DNA -\n(a) Plasmid DNA\n(b) Mitochondrial DNA\n(c) Chloroplast DNA\n(d) All\n\n206. DNA secondary structure stability depend on -\n(a) Number of Hydrogen bonds\n(b) Number of G.C content\n(c) Phosphodiester bond\n(d) Both (a) and (b)\n\n207. Central dogma in molecular biology was proposed by -\n(a) Francis Crick\n(b) Watson\n(c) Franklin\n(d) Wilkins\n\n208. Central dogma in molecular biology states that genetic information flows from -\n(a) DNA to mRNA and then to Protein\n(b) RNA to DNA and then to Protein\n(c) RNA to RNA and then to Protein\n(d) DNA to RNA and then to Protein\n\n209. Transcription and DNA replication have common -\n(a) Final product\n(b) Substrate\n(c) Template\n(d) All\n\n210. For Reverse transcription template is -\n(a) RNA\n(b) DNA\n(c) Protein\n(d) All\n\n211. Reverse transcription is done by -\n(a) Retrovirus\n(b) Virus with RNA genome\n(c) By virus with the help of reverse transcriptase\n(d) All\n\n212. Reverse transcriptase enzyme is -\n(a) DNA dependent DNA polymerase\n(b) RNA dependent RNA polymerase\n\n(c) DNA dependent RNA polymerase\n(d) RNA dependent DNA polymerase\n\n213. If the length of diploid DNA double helix in a typical mammalian cell is -\n(a) 2.2 meters\n(b) 1.1 meters\n(c) 3.5 nm\n(d) 2 meters\n\n214. DNA of prokaryotic cell is located in -\n(a) Cytoplasm\n(b) Nucleus\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) Ribosome\n\n215. Packaging of DNA occur for -\n(a) Prokaryotic cell\n(b) Eukaryotic cell\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) Virus\n\n216. In which phase of cell cycle in Eukaryotes DNA is most condensed -\n(a) M-phase\n(b) Metaphase\n(c) S-phase\n(d) G1 phase\n\n217. Which of the following is most condensed form of DNA -\n\n(a) Euchromatin\n(b) Heterochromatin\n(c) DNA\n(d) Metaphasic Chromosome\n\n218. DNA replication is semiconservative first experimentally proved in -\n(a) E. coli\n(b) Plants\n(c) Animals\n(d) Fungi\n\n219. During DNA replication, Okazaki fragments are used to elongate -\n(a) The leading strand towards replication fork\n(b) The lagging strand towards replication fork\n(c) The leading strand away from replication fork\n(d) The lagging strand away from the replication fork\n\n220. N15 and N14 used in Meselson and Stahl experiment differ in -\n(a) N14 is radioactive and N15 is non-radioactive\n(b) Both are light DNA\n(c) N14 shows less density than N15\n(d) None of the above\n\n221. Mark the correct statement -\n(a) Meselson and Stahl experiment and experiment on Vicia faba is carried out in same\nyear\n(b) DNA replication is semi-conservative was proposed first then its experimental proof\ncame\n\n(c) DNA in chromosome also replicate semi-conservatively proved by experiment on\nVicia faba\n(d) All are correct\n\n222. In Meselson & Stahl experiment after 4 generations number of N14N14 DNA is, if\nwe start with one cell with heavy DNA and grow in N14 source -\n(a) 14\n(b) 6\n(c) 30\n(d) None of these\n\n223. If generation time of E. coli is 20 min and if we start with 16 number of E. coli having\nlight DNA and grow it on heavy nitrogen source for 80 min, calculate cells having hybrid\nDNA -\n(a) 240\n(b) 256\n(c) 254\n223. If generation time of E. coli is 20 min and if we start with 16 number of E. coli having\nlight DNA and grow it on heavy nitrogen source for 80 min, calculate cells having hybrid\nDNA -\n(a) 240\n(b) 256\n(c) 254\n(d) 32\n\n224. In Meselson & Stahl experiment, percentage of hybrid DNA after five generations -\n(a) 12.5 percent\n(b) 6.25 percent\n(c) 25 percent\n\n(d) 50 percent\n\n225. If we obtain 12 cells with hybrid DNA after growing E. coli cells for five generations\non N14 source, then calculate how many cells initially were present with N15N15 DNA -\n(a) 6 cells\n(b) 12 cells\n(c) 18 cells\n(d) 24 cells\n\n226. If we obtain 20 cells with hybrid DNA after growing E. coli cells for fifty generations\non N14 source, then calculate how many cells initially were present with N15N15 DNA -\n(a) 2050\n(b) 10\n(c) 23\n(d) 50\n\n227. In a culture plate if N14 source was present, after 80 min twenty bacteria were\nhybrid, then how many bacteria are present in culture plate with N14N14 DNA at same\ntime -\n(a) 140\n(b) 160\n(c) 200\n(d) 100\n\n228. In Taylor experiment for semiconservative DNA replication, faba bean is grown in -\n(a) Heavy thymidine\n(b) Radioactive thymidine\n(c) Radioactive adenine\n(d) Heavy cytidine\n\n229. Which of the following is not true for DNA polymerase -\n(a) Uses template DNA\n(b) Substrate is dNTPs\n(c) Product is polynucleotide chain\n(d) Can add nucleotide at 5' end\n\n230. Which of the following can be substrate for DNA polymerase -\n(a) dAMP\n(b) UTP\n(c) dGDP\n(d) dCTP\n\n231. Which of the following enzyme not required in DNA replication -\n(a) RNA polymerase\n(b) Ligase\n(c) Endonuclease\n(d) DNA dependent DNA polymerase\n\n232. Which is correct about enzyme which produces primer during DNA replication -\n(a) It forms primer on both strands of DNA\n(b) It is DNA dependent RNA polymerase\n(c) Also known as primase and ribose nucleoside triphosphate is substrate\n(d) All of the above\n\n233. Mark the incorrect statement -\n(a) Primer synthesized in 5' to 3' direction on both leading and lagging strand\n(b) DNA dependent polymerase always polymerizes in 5' to 3' direction\n\n(c) Leading strand shows DNA replication in 5' to 3' direction and lagging in 3' to 5'\ndirection\n(d) Ligase catalyzes phosphodiester bond formation\n\n234. Enzyme which breaks H-bond to generate replication fork within replicon is -\n(a) Helicase\n(b) Topoisomerase\n(c) Ligase\n(d) DNA polymerase\n\n235. Which is incorrect statement -\n(a) Okazaki fragments are present in lagging strand\n(b) Okazaki fragments are joined by ligase\n(c) On leading strand repeated primer synthesis occur\n(d) On lagging strand repeated primer synthesis occur\n\n236. Number of replicons present in prokaryotes -\n(a) One\n(b) Two\n(c) Three\n(d) None\n\n237. Which of the following is not present in one replicon -\n(a) One origin\n(b) Two terminuses\n(c) Two replication forks\n(d) Single replication fork\n\n238. Mark the incorrect statement -\n(a) Replication fork moves away from origin\n(b) Replication fork moves towards terminus\n(c) Lagging strand DNA replication occurs away from replication fork\n(d) Leading strand DNA replication occurs away from replication fork\n\n239. Which is correct about Primase -\n(a) It is DNA polymerase\n(b) It is RNA polymerase\n(c) It is DNA dependent RNA polymerase\n(d) Both (a) and (c)\n\n240. DNA replication is different from transcription in -\n(a) Both occur in 5' to 3' direction\n(b) Both require DNA as template\n(c) Nucleoside triphosphate is substrate\n(d) Both require origin\n\n241. Mark the incorrectly matched -\n(a) Helicase О“ГҮГҙ break H-bond\n(b) SSB О“ГҮГҙ keep DNA single stranded\n(c) Topoisomerase О“ГҮГҙ decrease DNA negative supercoiling\n(d) DNA ligase О“ГҮГҙ link single nucleotide with polynucleotide chain\n\n242. Which is correct -\n(a) Replicon of prokaryotes is smaller than eukaryotic replicon\n(b) Eukaryotic replicon number is more than one\n(c) All replicons start replication once in a cell cycle\n\n(d) DNA replication of prokaryotes is slower than eukaryotes\n\n243. If in one replication fork total number of Okazaki fragments are 10 then total\nnumber of primers synthesized in replicon are -\n(a) 20\n(b) 22\n(c) 20\n(d) 5\n\n244. Which of the following process occurs once in a cell cycle -\n(a) DNA replication\n(b) Transcription\n(c) Translation\n(d) All\n\n245. Which of the following undergo replication -\n(a) Origin\n(b) Terminus\n(c) Heterochromatin\n(d) All\n\n246. Which of the following is true -\n(a) In one replicon two leading and two lagging strands present\n(b) One replicon has two terminus and one origin\n(c) Two replication forks generated at origin and move away from it\n(d) All are true\n\n247. Who experimentally proved the semiconservative mode of DNA replication -\n\n(a) Matthew Meselson\n(b) Franklin Stahl\n(c) Both (a) and (b)\n(d) Watson and Crick\n\n248. Similar experiments like Meselson and Stahl were performed by Taylor in 1958. The\nexperimental organism of Taylor was -\n(a) Vicia faba\n(b) Fungi\n(c) E. coli\n(d) Protista\n\n249. Radioisotope used by Taylor in his experiment was -\n(a) Iron\n(b) Titanium\n(c) Thymidine\n(d) Copper\n\n250. DNA polymerase is -\n(a) DNA dependent\n(b) DNA independent\n(c) RNA dependent\n(d) RNA independent\n\n251. DNA polymerization rate of DNA po