\nQ43. Long ribbon-shaped pollen present inО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Hydrilla\n(2) Vallisneria\n(3) Zostera\n(4) Water lily\n\nQ44. Mucilaginous covering to make pollen unwettable is present inО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Hydrilla\n(2) Zostera\n(3) both 1 and 2\n(4) Water lily\n\nQ45. Which of the following group is most dominating pollinating agentО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Bird, bat and gecko lizard\n(2) Bee, butterflies and beetle\n(3) Wasp, bee and water\n(4) Lemur, rodents and ants\n\nQ46. Insect pollinated flower is small in size. To overcome this limitation they showО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Colour\n(2) Nectar\n(3) Grouped in cluster\n(4) Fragrance\n\nQ47. Insects are attracted towards flower because of presence ofО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Nectar and colour\n(2) Colour and fragrance\n(3) Nectar and fragrance\n(4) all of the above\n\nQ48. Yucca plant provides mothО“ГҮГ¶\n\n(1) Edible nectar\n(2) Space for egg laying\n(3) both 1 and 2\n(4) all wrong\n\nQ49. Inbreeding depression is not present inО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Monoecious flower\n(2) Cleistogamous flower\n(3) Dioecious plant\n(4) Dioecious flower\n\nQ50. In breeding depression, it is overcome byО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Self-incompatibility\n(2) Dioecious flower\n(3) Protandrous condition\n(4) all\n\nQ51. Morphological mechanism to prevent inbreedingО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Self-incompatibility\n(2) Herkogamy\n(3) Dicliny\n(4) all of the above\n\nQ52. Genetic mechanism to prevent inbreedingО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Self-incompatibility\n(2) Herkogamy\n(3) Dicliny\n(4) all of the above\n\nQ53. Self-incompatibility is not possible if flower isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Monoecious\n(2) Dioecious\n(3) Cleistogamous\n(4) all of the above\n\nQ54. Self-incompatibility is not possible if plant isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Monoecious\n(2) Dioecious\n(3) With chasmogamous flower\n(4) all of the above\n\nQ55. Both self-incompatibility and inbreeding absent inО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Papaya\n\n(2) Castor\n(3) Sweet potato\n(4) both 1 and 2\n\nQ56. Incompatible and self-incompatible pollen come from flower respectivelyО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Same and different species flower\n(2) Different and same species flower\n(3) both same species flower\n(4) both different species flower\n\nQ57. Rejection of pollen is due to chemical dialogue between pollen andО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Stigma\n(2) Pistil\n(3) Style\n(4) none of the above\n\nQ58. Which of the following event is not part of pollenО“ГҮГҙpistil interactionО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pollen germination\n(2) Pollen tube growth\n(3) Pollination\n(4) all\n\nQ59. Pollen tube carries content in style when pollen shed at two-cell stage. Contents\nareО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Vegetative cell nucleus and two male gametes\n(2) One male gamete and vegetative cell nucleus\n(3) Two male gametes only\n(4) Two vegetative cell nucleus\n\nQ60. Pollen tube carries content in style when pollen shed at three-cell stage. Contents\nareО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Vegetative cell nucleus and two male gametes\n(2) One male gamete and vegetative cell nucleus\n(3) Two male gametes only\n(4) Two vegetative cell nucleus\n\nQ61. Bagging is required inО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) When stigma becomes receptive\n(2) Dioecious flower\n(3) Before stigma becomes receptive\n(4) At the time of pollination\n\nQ62. Syngamy term can be used forО“ГҮГ¶\n\n(1) Fusion of both male and female gamete\n(2) Fusion of two male gametes\n(3) Fusion of male gamete with polar nuclei\n(4) both 1 and 3\n\nQ63. After double fertilization, normally how many cells degenerateО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Four\n(2) Five\n(3) Six\n(4) Three\n\nQ64. A hexaploid monoecious flowering plant has ploidy of nucellus, vegetative cell,\naleurone layer, cotyledon respectivelyО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) 2n, n, 3n, 2n\n(2) 6n, 3n, 9n, 6n\n(3) 6n, 3n, 6n, 9n\n(4) 2n, 3n, 6n, 4n\n\nQ65. A tetraploid dioecious male plant crossed with hexaploid dioecious female plant\nof same species. Then ploidy of integument, epicotyl and endosperm isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) 6n, 4n, 7n\n(2) 6n, 3n, 7n\n(3) 6n, 5n, 2n\n(4) 6n, 5n, 7n\n\nQ66. Which pair of tissues is genetically identical in pea flower showing autogamyО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Nucellus and epicotyl\n(2) Aleurone layer and integument\n(3) Cotyledon and hilum\n(4) Nu