and female gamete\n(2) Fusion of two male gametes\n(3) Fusion of male gamete with polar nuclei\n(4) Both (1) and (3)\n\nQ183. Which is not a false fruitО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Strawberry\n(2) Cashew\n(3) Apple\n(4) Mustard\n\nQ184. Mark the correctly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Viola О“ГҮГҙ Cleistogamous\n(2) Oxalis О“ГҮГҙ Only xenogamy\n(3) Coconut О“ГҮГҙ Dioecious plant\n(4) Orchids О“ГҮГҙ Single ovule\n\nQ185. Mark the correctly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Filament proximal end О“ГҮГҙ Anther attach\n(2) Microsporangia О“ГҮГҙ Have egg\n\n(3) Longitudinal groove О“ГҮГҙ Separate two lobes\n(4) Pollen sac О“ГҮГҙ Have pollen\n\nQ186. Mark the incorrectly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pollen allergy О“ГҮГҙ Parthenium\n(2) Pollen bank О“ГҮГҙ О“ГҮГҙ196в”¬в–‘C, liquid nitrogen\n(3) Exine О“ГҮГҙ Released by vegetative cell\n(4) Intine О“ГҮГҙ Continuous layer\n\nQ187. Mark the incorrectly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Vegetative cell О“ГҮГҙ Irregular shape of nucleus\n(2) Generative cell О“ГҮГҙ Produces male gamete\n(3) PMC О“ГҮГҙ Diploid\n(4) Most pollination О“ГҮГҙ 3-cell stage\n\nQ188. Mark the incorrectly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Flower with foul smell О“ГҮГҙ Flies and beetle\n(2) Yucca plant О“ГҮГҙ Moth\n(3) Hydrilla О“ГҮГҙ Pollination by insect\n(4) Zostera О“ГҮГҙ Ribbon-shaped pollen\n\nQ189. Mark the incorrectly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Stigma receptivity and anther maturity not synchronized О“ГҮГҙ Outbreeding devices\n(2) Castor О“ГҮГҙ Unisexual flower and monoecious plant\n(3) Self-incompatibility О“ГҮГҙ Not a genetic mechanism\n(4) Amorphophallus О“ГҮГҙ Space for egg laying\n\nQ190. Mark the correctly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Bagging О“ГҮГҙ Done in bisexual and staminate flower\n(2) Emasculation О“ГҮГҙ Done in bisexual and pistillate flower\n(3) Emasculation О“ГҮГҙ Done only in bisexual flower\n(4) Pollen tube О“ГҮГҙ Develop from exine\n\nQ191. Mark the incorrectly matched pairО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Two-cell stage pollen О“ГҮГҙ Two male gametes form in stigma\n(2) Pollen germination О“ГҮГҙ By boron\n(3) Both male gametes released into О“ГҮГҙ Synergids\n(4) Nucleus of vegetative cell О“ГҮГҙ Regular in shape\n\nQ192. Assertion: Double fertilization is characteristic feature of angiosperms.\nReason: Double fertilization involves two fusions.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ193. Assertion: The largest cell of the embryo sac is the central cell.\nReason: It consists of fused nuclei.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ194. Assertion: Endosperm is a nutritive tissue and it is triploid.\nReason: Endosperm is formed by fusion of secondary nucleus to second male gamete.\nIt is used by developing embryo.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ195. Assertion: Megaspore mother cell undergoes meiotic division.\nReason: All four megaspores form female gametophyte.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ196. Assertion: NonО“ГҮГҰalbuminous seeds have no residual endosperm.\nReason: The endosperm is completely consumed during embryo development.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ197. Assertion: Mango is a true fruit.\n\nReason: The thalamus also contributes to formation of fruit in false fruits.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ198. Assertion: Pollen grains from male parent are mostly transferred to the stigma in\nthe female parent by some external agency.\nReason: This is because the male flowers or male organs have no internal device to\nreach the female in another flower.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ199. Assertion: The pollen sterility has been attributed to the malfunctioning of\ntapetum.\nReason: Premature degeneration of the tapetum deprives the developing spores of its\nnutrition.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ200. Assertion: Autogamy is a transfer of pollen grains from an anther to the stigma of\nthe same flower on the same plant.\nReason: Xenogamy is pollination between two flowers on different plants.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ201. Assertion: Insects visit flowers to gather honey.\nReason: Attraction of flowers prevents the insects from damaging other parts of the\nplant.\n\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ202. Assertion: Pollen mother cells (PMCs) are the first male gametophytic cells.\nReason: Each PMC gives rise to two pollens.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ203. Assertion: Exine of a pollen grain is made up of sporopollenins which are\nresistant to high temperatures, strong acids or alkali as well as enzymatic degradation.\nReason: Sporopollenins are absent in the region of germ pores.\n(1) Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(2) Both Assertion and Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of\nAssertion\n(3) Assertion is true but Reason is false\n(4) Both Assertion and Reason are false\n\nQ204. In figure given below, find out the type of seed and identify coleoptile, coleorhiza\nand epiblastО“ГҮГ¶\n\n(1) Monocots О“ГҮГҙ A, B and C\n(2) Dicots О“ГҮГҙ F, A and C\n(3) Monocots О“ГҮГҙ B, G and D\n(4) Dicots О“ГҮГҙ D, E and A\n\nQ205. Match the following columnsО“ГҮГ¶\nColumn I\nA. Antipodal\nB. Central cell\nC. MMC\nD. Endosperm\n\nColumn II\n1. 3n\n2. 2n\n3. (n + n)\n4. n\n\nCodes:\n A B C D\n(1) 4 3 1 2\n(2) 3 2 1 4\n(3) 4 3 2 1\n(4) 3 4 1 2\n\nQ206. Match the following columnsО“ГҮГ¶\nColumn I\nA. Wind\nB. Water\nC. Insects\nD. Bird\n\nColumn II\n1. Anemophily\n2. Hydrophily\n3. Entomophily\n4. Ornithophily\n\nCodes:\n A B C D\n(1) 1 2 3 4\n(2) 1 3 2 4\n(3) 4 2 3 1\n(4) 2 3 4 1\n\nQ207. Match the following columnsО“ГҮГ¶\nColumn I\n\nA. Monocarpellary\nB. Multicarpellary\nC. Syncarpous\nD. Apocarpous\n\nColumn II\n1. Free pistil\n2. Fused pistil\n3. Many pistil\n4. Single pistil\n\nCodes:\n  A B C D\n(1) 1 2 3 4\n(2) 4 3 2 1\n(3) 3 4 2 1\n(4) 4 3 1 2\n\nQ208. Match the following columnsО“ГҮГ¶\nColumn I\nA. Ovary\nB. Ovule\nC. Wall of fruit\nD. Fleshy fruits\nE. Dry fruits\n\nColumn II\n1. Groundnut, mustard\n2. Guava, orange, mango\n3. Pericarp\n4. Seed\n5. Fruit\n\nCodes\n         A B C D E\n   (1) 5 4 3 2 1\n   (2) 1 2 3 4 5\n   (3) 1 3 2 4 5\n   (4) 5 4 1 2 3\n\nQ209. What is the correct sequence of development in microsporogenesisО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pollen grain, Sporogenous tissue, Microspore tetrad, PMC, Male gametes\n(2) Sporogenous tissue, Microspore tetrad, PMC, Male gametes\n\n(3) Pollen grain, Male gametes, PMC, Microspore tetrad, Sporogenous tissue\n(4) Sporogenous tissue, PMC, Microspore tetrad, Pollen grain, Male gametes\n\nQ210. Strategies to prevent selfО“ГҮГҰpollination areО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Dioecy\n(2) SelfО“ГҮГҰincompatibility\n(3) Both (a) and (b)\n(4) None of these\n\nQ211. The portion of embryonal axis above the level of cotyledons isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Epicotyl\n(2) Hypocotyl\n(3) Plumule\n(4) Radicle\n\nQ212. Perisperm isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Residual nucellus\n(2) Residual endosperm\n(3) Covering of fruit\n(4) None of these\n\nQ213. Name the part of gynoecium that determines the compatible nature of pollen\ngrainО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pistil\n(2) Ovary\n(3) Ovum\n(4) Ovule\n\nQ214. In over 60 per cent of angiosperms, pollen grains are shed atО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) 2О“ГҮГҰcelled stage\n(2) 3О“ГҮГҰcelled stage\n(3) 4О“ГҮГҰcelled stage\n(4) 1О“ГҮГҰcelled stage\n\nQ215. The end product of sexual reproduction isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Flowers and leaves\n(2) Root and stem\n(3) Fruits and seed\n(4) Male and female gametes\n\nQ216. Polar nuclei are presentО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Below the antipodal cells\n(2) Below the egg apparatus\n\n(3) Above the egg apparatus\n(4) All of the above are correct\n\nQ217. Egg apparatus consists ofО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) 2 synergids + two egg\n(2) 3 synergids + two egg\n(3) 1 synergid + two egg\n(4) 2 synergids + one egg\n\nQ218. All the events from pollen deposition on the stigma until pollen tubes enter the\novules are together referred to asО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pollination\n(2) PollenО“ГҮГҰPistil interaction\n(3) DoubleО“ГҮГҰFertilization\n(4) Apomixis\n\nQ219. Dioecious flowering plants preventО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Autogamy and geitonogamy\n(2) Geitonogamy and xenogamy\n(3) Cleistogamy and xenogamy\n(4) Autogamy and xenogamy\n\nQ220. Which of the following event is not a postО“ГҮГҰfertilisation eventО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Development of endosperm\n(2) Formation of embryo\n(3) Transformation of ovary into fruit\n(4) Formation of mature embryo sac\n\nQ221. Pollen grain representsО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Male gametophyte\n(2) Male sporophyte\n(3) Female gametophyte\n(4) Female sporophyte\n\nQ222. Which of the following has proved helpful in preserving pollen as fossilsО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Pollen kitt\n(2) PectoО“ГҮГҰcellulosic intine\n(3) Oil content\n(4) Sporopollenin\n\nQ223. Transfer of pollen from anther to stigma of a different plant is calledО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Autogamy\n(2) Syngamy\n\n(3) Geitonogamy\n(4) Xenogamy\n\nQ224. Filiform apparatus are present onО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Egg cell\n(2) Antipodals\n(3) Central cell\n(4) Synergids\n\nQ225. In grass family the cotyledon is calledО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Coleorhiza\n(2) Scutellum\n(3) Epicotyl\n(4) Coleoptile\n\nQ226. Flowers possess wellО“ГҮГҰexposed stamens and feathery stigma are pollinated byО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Water\n(2) Wind\n(3) Bees\n(4) Flies\n\nQ227. Which structure guides the entry of pollen tube into the embryo sacО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Antipodal cell\n(2) Filiform apparatus\n(3) Egg apparatus\n(4) Integument\n\nQ228. Site of sexual reproduction in plants isО“ГҮГ¶\n(1) Internode\n(2) Fruits\n(3) Flower\n(4) Leaflets\n\nAnswer key\nQUESTION ANSWER QUESTION ANSWER QUESTION ANSWER QUESTION ANSWER\n