anation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-4 B-3 C-1 D -2"}, {"text": "List I: A. Nucleotide B. Adenylic acid C. Adenine D. Alanine\\r\\nList II: I. Nitrogen base II. Nucleotide III. Nucleoside IV. Amino acid\\r\\nChoose the option with all correct matches:", "options": ["A-3 B-2 C-1 D-4", "A-2 B -3 C-1 D-4", "A-3 B-4 C-2 D -1", "A-3 B-2 C-4 D-1"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-3 B-2 C-1 D-4"}, {"text": " In frog, the Renal portal system is a special venous connection that acts to \\r\\nlink:", "options": ["Kidney & Intenstine ", "Kindey & Lower part of Body ", "Liver & Intestine ", "Liver & Kidney "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Kindey & Lower part of Body "}, {"text": " Which of the following are the post-transcriptional events in an eukaryotic cell\\nA. Transport of pre-mRNA to cytoplasm prior to splicing. \\r\\nB. Removal of introns and joining of exons. \\r\\nC. Addition of methyl group at 5' end of hnRNA. \\r\\nD. Addition of adenine residues at 3' end of hnRNA. E. Base pairing of two \\r\\ncomplementary RNAs.\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["B,C,E only ", "A,B,D only ", "A,B,C only ", "B,C,D only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "B,C,D only "}, {"text": "Assertion (A): Both wind and water pollinated flowers are not very colourful and do not \\r\\nproduce nectar. \\r\\nReason (R): The flowers produce enormous amount of pollen grains in wind and water \\r\\npollinated flowers. \\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given \\r\\nbelow:", "options": ["A is true But R is false ", "A is false But R is true ", "Both A & R are true & R is the Correct explanation of A ", "Both A & R are true But R is Not the correct explanation of A "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Both A & R are true & R is the Correct explanation of A "}, {"text": "Epiphytes that are growing on a mango branch is an example of which of the following?", "options": ["Predation", "Amensalism ", "Commensalism ", "Mutualism"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Commensalism "}, {"text": " Find the correct statements:\\r\\nA. In human pregnancy, the major organ systems are formed at the end of 12 weeks.\\r\\nB. In human pregnancy the major organ systems are formed at the end of 8 weeks. \\r\\nC. In human pregnancy heart is formed after one month of gestation. \\r\\nD. In human pregnancy, limbs and digits develop by the end of second month. \\r\\nE. In human pregnancy the appearance of hair is usually observed in the fifth month. \\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["B,C,D only ", "A,C & D only ", "A,B ,C only ", "B & D only"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "B,C,D only "}, {"text": "Identify the part of a bio-reactor which is used as a foam breaker from the given ", "options": ["DX", "C", "A", "B"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"text": "114. Consider the following statements regarding function of adrenal medullary \\r\\nhormones:\\r\\nA. It causes pupillary constriction \\r\\nB. It is a emergency hormone\\r\\nC. It causes dilation\\r\\nD. It increases strength of heart contraction \\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["A,C & D only ", "B & D only ", "A & B only ", "C & D only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "B & D only "}, {"text": " Read the following statements on plant growth and development.\\r\\nA. Parthenocarpy can be induced by auxins. \\r\\nB. Plant growth regulators can be involved in promotion as well as inhibition of growth. \\r\\nC. Dedifferentiation is a pre-requisite for re-differentiation. \\r\\nD. Abscisic acid is a plant growth promoter.\\r\\nE. Apical dominance promotes the growth of lateral buds. Choose the option with all correct statement", "options": ["A,D,E only ", "B,D,E only ", "A,B,C only", "A,C,E only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "B,D,E only "}, {"text": " Which of the following hormones released from the pituitary is actually \\r\\nsynthesized in the hypothalamus?", "options": ["Follicle-stimulating hormone ( FSH )", "Adrenocorticotropohic hormone ( ACTH ) ", "Luteinizing Hormone ( LH ) ", "None of the above "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Follicle-stimulating hormone ( FSH )"}, {"text": "117. Which of the following is an example of non-distilled alcoholic beverage \\r\\nproduced by yeast?", "options": ["Beer", "Rum", "Whisky ", "Brandy "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Beer"}, {"text": "What is the pattern of inheritance for polygenic trait?", "options": ["Autosomal Dominant Patter. ", "X-linked recessive inheritance pattern ", "Mendelian inheritance pattern ", "Non-Mendelian inheritance pattern"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Mendelian inheritance pattern "}, {"text": "Match List - I with List О“ГҮГҙ II'\\r\\nList - I: \\r\\nО“ГҮГҝA. Head \\r\\nB. Middle piece \\r\\nC. Acrosome \\r\\nD. Tail\\r\\nList - II: \\\\\\r\\nI. Enzymes \\\\\\r\\nII. Sperm motility \\r\\nIII. Energy \\r\\nIV. Genetic material\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["A-3 B -5 C -1 D- 2", "A-3 B-2 C-1 D -4", "A-4 B-3 C-1 D -2", "A-1 B-3 C-1 D-4"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-3 B-2 C-1 D -4"}, {"text": " Which of the following is an example of a zygomorphic flower", "options": ["Pea", "Chili ", "Petunia ", "Datura"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Pea"}, {"text": "121. Which of the following organisms can fix nitrogen?", "options": ["Azotobacter ", "Oscilatoria ", "Anabaena ", "Nostoc"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Nostoc"}, {"text": "Which one of the following is an example of ex situ conservation? ", "options": ["Zoos & botanical garden", "Protected areas ", "National Park ", "Wildlife sanctuary "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Protected areas "}, {"text": "Who is known as the father of Ecology in India?", "options": ["Ram Udhar ", "Birbal sahni", "S.R.Kashyap", "R.mishra "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "R.mishra "}, {"text": "Statement I: In the RNA world, RNA is considered the first genetic material evolved to \\r\\ncarry out essential life processes. RNA acts as a genetic material and also as a catalyst \\r\\nfor some important biochemical reactions in living systems. Being reactive, RNA is \\r\\nunstable. \\r\\nStatement II: DNA evolved from RNA and is a more stable genetic material. Its double \\r\\nhelical strand, being complementary, resists changes by evolving repairing mechanism. \\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the \\r\\noptions given below:", "options": ["Both statement are correct ", "Statement 1 is correct & Statement 2 is incorrect", "Statement 1 is incorrect & Statement 2 is Correct ", "Both statement are wrong "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Both statement are correct "}, {"text": "Statement I: Transfer RNAs and ribosomal RNA do not interact with mRNA.\\nStatement II: RNA interference (RNAi) takes place in all eukaryotic organisms as a \\r\\nmethod of cellular defense. In the light of the above statements, choose the most \\r\\nappropriate answer from the options below:", "options": ["Both statement are wrong ", "Statement 1 is correct & Statement 2 is incorrect ", "Statement 1 is incorrect but Statement 2 is correct ", "Both statement are correct "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Statement 1 is incorrect but Statement 2 is correct "}, {"text": "Match List - I with List - II.\\r\\nList - I: \\r\\nA. Kidney \\r\\nB. Gastro-intestinal tract \\r\\nC. Adrenal Cortex\\r\\nD. Heart\\r\\nList - II: \\r\\nI. Erythropoietin \\r\\nII. Aldosterone \\r\\nIII. Atrial natriuretic factor \\r\\nIV. Secretin\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["A-1 B-3 C-4 D-2", "A-2 B-1 C-4 D-2", "A-2 B-3 C-2 D-4", "A-5 B-2 C-3 D-1"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-1 B-3 C-4 D-2"}, {"text": "All living members of the class Cyclostomata are:", "options": ["Symbiotic ", "Ectoparasite ", "Free living ", "Endoparasite "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Ectoparasite "}, {"text": "Streptokinase produced by bacterium Streptococcus is used for:", "options": ["Liver disease Treatment ", "Removing Clots from Blood Vessels ", "Curd production ", "Ethanol Production "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Removing Clots from Blood Vessels "}, {"text": "Role of the water vascular system in Echinoderms is:\\r\\nA. Respiration and Locomotion \\r\\nB. Excretion and Locomotion \\r\\nC. Cure, transport and food \\r\\nD. Digestion and Respiration\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options below:", "options": ["B & C only ", "A & D only ", "A only ", "B D & E only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A only "}, {"text": "Match List I with List II.\\r\\nList I \\r\\nA. Pteridophyte\\r\\nB. Bryophyte \\r\\nC. Angiosperm \\r\\nD. Gymnosperm\\r\\nList II \\r\\nI. Salvia \\r\\nII. Ginkgo\\r\\nIII. Polytrichum \\r\\nIV. Riccia\\r\\nChoose the option with all correct matches.", "options": ["A-3 B-4 C-1 D -2", "A-4 B-3 C-2 D-1", "A-3 B-4 C-2 D-1", "A-4 B-3 C-1 D-2"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-3 B-4 C-1 D -2"}, {"text": "Which are correct:\\r\\nA. Computed tomography and magnetic resonance imaging detect cancers of internal \\r\\norgans. \\r\\nB. Chemotherapeutic drugs are used to kill non-cancerous cells. \\r\\nC. в•¬в–’-interferon activate the cancer patientsО“ГҮГ– immune system and helps in destroying the \\r\\ntumour. \\r\\nD. Chemotherapeutic drugs are biological response modifiers. In the case of leukaemia \\r\\nblood cell counts are decreased.\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["C & D only ", "A & C only ", "B & D only ", "D & E only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A & C only "}, {"text": "What are the potential drawbacks in adoption of IVF method?\\r\\nA. High fatality risk to mother \\r\\nB. Expensive instruments and reagents \\r\\nC. Husband/wife necessary for keeping donors \\r\\nD. Less adoption of orphans \\r\\nE. Not available in India \\r\\nF. Possibility that the early embryo does not survive\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["A B C only ", "A B F only ", "A B D Only ", "A B C  D only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A B F only "}, {"text": "Consider the following:\\r\\nA. The reductive division for the human female gametogenesis starts earlier than that of \\r\\nthe male gametogenesis. \\r\\nB. The gap between the first meiotic division and the second meiotic division is much \\r\\nshorter for males compared to females. \\r\\nC. The first polar body is associated with the formation of the primary oocyte. \\r\\nD. Luteinizing Hormone (LH) surge leads to disintegration of the endometrium and onset \\r\\nof menstrual bleeding.\\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["A & B are true ", "B & C are true ", "C & A are true ", "All are wrong "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A & B are true "}, {"text": "In bryophytes, the gametophyte help in which one of the following?", "options": ["Nutrient Absorption ", "Gaseous Exchange ", "Sexsual Reproduction ", "Asexsual Reproduction "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Sexsual Reproduction "}, {"text": "Given below are two statements: one is labelled as Assertion (A) and the other \\r\\nis labelled as Reason (R).\\r\\nAssertion (A): The primary function of the Golgi apparatus is to package the materials \\r\\nmade by the endoplasmic reticulum and deliver it to intracellular targets and outside \\r\\nthe cell\\r\\nReason (R): Vesicles containing materials made by the endoplasmic reticulum fuse with \\r\\nthe cis face of the Golgi apparatus, and they are modified and released from the trans \\r\\nface of the Golgi apparatus.\\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below", "options": ["A is true But R is false ", "A is false but R is true ", "Both A & R are true and R is the Correct explanation of A ", "Both A & R are true But R is not the Correct explanation Of A "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Both A & R are true and R is the Correct explanation of A "}, {"text": "Which one of the following statements refers to reductionist Biology ? ", "options": ["Chemical approach to study & understand living organisms ", "Behavioral approach to study & understand living organisms ", "Physiochemical approach to study &  understand living organisms ", "Physiological approach to study & understand living organisms"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Physiochemical approach to study &  understand living organisms "}, {"text": "After maturation, in primary lymphoid organs, the lymphocytes migrate for \\r\\ninteraction with antigens to secondary lymphoid organs / tissue(s) like:\\r\\nA. thymus \\r\\nB. bone marrow\\r\\nC. spleen \\r\\nD. lymph nodes \\r\\nE. PeyerО“ГҮГ–s patches \\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["E A B only ", "C D E only ", "B C D only ", "A B C only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "C D E only "}, {"text": " Match List I with List II:\\r\\nList I: \\r\\nA. The Evil Quartet \\r\\nB. Ex situ conservation \\r\\nC. Lantana camara \\r\\nD. Dodo\\r\\nList II: \\r\\nI. Cryopreservation\\\\\\r\\nII. Alien species invasion\\nIII. Causes of biodiversity losses \\r\\nIV. Extinction\\r\\nChoose the option with all correct matches:", "options": ["A-3 B-4 C-2 D-1", "A-3 B-1 C-4 D-2", "A-3 B-1 C-2 D-4", "A-3 B-1 C-2 D-4"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A-3 B-1 C-2 D-4"}, {"text": "How many meiotic and mitotic divisions are needed for the development of a \\r\\nmature female gametophyte from the megaspore mother cell in an angiosperm \\r\\nplant?", "options": ["1 Meiosis & 3 Mitosis ", "No Meisosis & 2 Mitosis ", "2 Meiosis & 3 Mitosis ", "1 Meisosis & 2 Mitosis "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "1 Meiosis & 3 Mitosis "}, {"text": " Which of the following type of immunity is present at the time of birth and is a \\r\\nnon-specific type of defence in the human body?", "options": ["Cell-Mediated immunity", "Humoral immunity ", "Acquired immunity ", "Innate immunity "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Innate immunity "}, {"text": " Given below are two statements:\\r\\nStatement I: Fig fruit is a non-vegetarian fruit as it has enclosed fig wasps in it. \\r\\nStatement II: Fig wasp and fig tree exhibit mutual relationship as fig wasp completes its \\r\\nlife cycle in fig fruit and fig fruit gets pollinated by fig wasp.\\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below\\n", "options": ["Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorrect ", "Statement 1 is incorrect but statement 2 is correct ", "Both statement are correct ", "Both statement are wrong"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Statement 1 is incorrect but statement 2 is correct "}, {"text": "Given below are two statements: One is labelled as Assertion (A) and the other \\r\\nis labelled as Reason (R).\\r\\nAssertion (A): Cells of the tapetum possess dense cytoplasm and generally have more \\r\\nthan one nucleus.\\r\\nReason (R): Presence of more than one nucleus in the tapetum increases the efficiency \\r\\nof nourishing the developing microspore mother cells. \\r\\nIn light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below", "options": ["A is true But R is false ", "A IS FALSE BUT R is true ", "Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is correct explanation of Assertion ", "Both Assertion and Reason are true But Reason is NOT the correct explanation of A "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Both Assertion and Reason are true and Reason is correct explanation of Assertion "}, {"text": " From the statements given below choose the correct option:\\r\\nA. The eukaryotic ribosomes are 80S and prokaryotic ribosomes are 70S. О“ГҮГҝ\\r\\nB. Each ribosome has two sub-units. \\r\\nC. The two sub-units of 80S ribosome are 60S and 40S while that of 70S are 50S and \\r\\n30S. \\r\\nD. The two sub-units of 80S ribosome are 60S and 20S and that of 70S are 50S and 20S. \\r\\nE. The two sub-units of 80S are 60S and 30S and that of 70S are 50S and 30S.", "options": ["A,B,E are true ", "B,D,E are true ", "A,B,C are true ", "A,B,D are true "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "A,B,C are true "}, {"text": "Which one of the following enzymes contains О“ГҮГҝHaemО“ГҮГ– as the prosthetic group?", "options": ["Succinate dehydrogenase ", "Catalase ", "RuBisCO", "Carbonic anhydrase "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Catalase "}, {"text": " What is the name of the blood vessel that carries deoxygenated blood from the \\r\\nbody to the heart in a frog?", "options": ["Pulmonary vein ", "Vena Cava ", "Aorta ", "Pulmonary artery"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Pulmonary artery"}, {"text": "Given below are the stages in the life cycle of pteridophytes. Arrange the \\r\\nfollowing stages in the correct sequence.\\r\\nA. Prothallus stage \\r\\nB. Meiosis in spore mother cells \\r\\nC. Fertilisation \\r\\nD. Formation of archegonia and antheridia in gametophyte\\r\\nE. Transfer of antherozoids to the archegonia in presence of water. Choose the correct \\r\\nanswer from the options given below:", "options": ["D E C A B ", "E D C B A ", "B A D E C", "B A E C D"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "B A D E C"}, {"text": " The blue and white selectable markers have been developed which \\r\\ndifferentiate recombinant colonies from non-recombinant colonies on the basis of \\r\\ntheir ability to produce colour in the presence of a chromogenic substrate. Given \\r\\nbelow are two statements about this method:\\r\\nStatement I: The blue coloured colonies have DNA insert in the plasmid and they are \\r\\nidentified as recombinant colonies. \\r\\nStatement II: The colonies without blue colour have DNA insert in the plasmid and are \\r\\nidentified as recombinant colonies.\\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below", "options": ["Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorrect ", "Statement 1 is incorrect but statement is correct ", "Both statement 1 & 2 are Correct ", "Both statement are wrong "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Both statement 1 & 2 are Correct "}, {"text": "Which of the following microbes is not involved in the preparation of \\r\\nhousehold products?\\r\\nA. Aspergillus niger \\r\\nB. Lactobacillus \\r\\nC. Trichoderma polysporum \\r\\nD. Saccharomyces cerevisiae \\r\\nE. Propionibacterium sharmanii \\r\\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below:", "options": ["C & D only ", "C & E only ", "A & B only ", "A & C only "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "C & E only "}, {"text": " Silencing of specific mRNA is possible via RNAi because of О“ГҮГҙ", "options": ["Complementary tRNA", "Non-complementary ssRNA", "Complementary dsRNA", "Inhibition ssRNA"], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Complementary dsRNA"}, {"text": "The complex I of mitochondrial electron transport chain is also known as", "options": ["Cytochrome c oxidase ", "NADH dehydrogenase ", "Cytochrome bc1", "Succinate dehydrogenase "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "NADH dehydrogenase "}, {"text": "While trying to find out the characteristic of a newly found animal, a \\r\\nresearcher did the histology of that animal and observed a cavity with presence of \\r\\nmesodermal tissue towards the body wall but no mesodermal tissue was observed \\r\\ntowards the alimentary canal. What could be the possible coelome of that animal?", "options": ["Schizocoelomate ", "Spongocoelomate ", "Acoelomate", "Presudocoelomate "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Presudocoelomate "}, {"text": "Given below are two statements:\\r\\nStatement I: In a floral formula О“ГЁГІ stands for zygomorphic nature of the flower, and G \\r\\nstands for inferior ovary. \\r\\nStatement II: In a floral formula О“ГЁГІ stands for actinomorphic nature of the flower and G \\r\\nstands for superior ovary. \\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given \\r\\nbelow:", "options": ["Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorrect ", "Statement 1 is incorrect but statement 2 is correct ", "Both statement are wrong ", "Both statement are correct "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorrect "}, {"text": "Given below are two statements: О“ГҮГҝ\\r\\nStatement I: In ecosystem, there is unidirectional flow of energy from producers to \\r\\nconsumers. \\r\\nStatement II: Ecosystems are exempted from 2nd law of thermodynamics. \\r\\nIn the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the \\r\\noptions given below:", "options": ["Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorrect ", "Statement 1 is incorrect but statement 2 is correct ", "Both statement are correct ", "Both statement are wrong "], "imageUrl": null, "explanation": "", "correctAnswer": "Statement 1 is correct but statement 2 is incorr